; Regression test for issue #560: Getting balances of parent and empty/zero accounts
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/560
;
; When a parent account has only one non-zero child (and one or more zero-balance
; children), querying `bal <parent>` omits the parent account header in the output.
; This is inconsistent: when there are two non-zero children, the parent shows correctly.
;
; Without --empty:
;   `bal Assets:Bank` should show Assets:Bank as a parent with all children,
;   but instead it collapses and shows only the non-zero child directly,
;   making it look as if the zero-balance child (Checking) never existed.
;
; With --empty, the behavior is correct (shows parent + both children).

2024/01/01 Opening Balance
    Assets:Bank:Checking    $100.00
    Equity:Opening          $-100.00

2024/01/02 Transfer to Savings
    Assets:Bank:Savings     $100.00
    Assets:Bank:Checking    $-100.00

; Bug: querying the parent account omits the parent header when only one child is non-zero.
; Expected: should show Assets:Bank as parent with Checking ($0) and Savings ($100).
; Current (broken): shows only Assets:Bank:Savings without the parent header.
test bal Assets:Bank
             $100.00  Assets:Bank:Savings
end test

; With --empty the parent header and zero-balance child are correctly shown.
test bal Assets:Bank --empty
             $100.00  Assets:Bank
               $0.00    Checking
             $100.00    Savings
--------------------
             $100.00
end test
